# Cloudflare Pages response headers.
#
# Why this file exists: the app is code-split into content-hashed chunks under
# /assets/ (e.g. /assets/Pricing-DEDgDZ0X.js). Each deploy produces new hashes.
# If a browser caches an HTML shell, that stale HTML keeps referencing chunk
# names from the previous deploy - names the CDN no longer has - and the
# dynamic import() fails, showing the error screen on an otherwise healthy site.
#
# IMPORTANT about precedence: Cloudflare Pages applies EVERY matching rule and
# JOINS duplicate headers with a comma - it does NOT do "last rule wins". A
# request under /assets/ matches both rules below, so without intervention the
# asset would get "no-cache, ..., immutable" and no-cache would win, defeating
# the long cache. The "! Cache-Control" line removes the value inherited from
# /* before the /assets/* block sets its own.
#
#   * All navigations / HTML shells (including the prerendered per-route shells
#     like /pricing/): never cache, always revalidate, so a new deploy's HTML
#     reaches visitors immediately.
#   * /assets/* : content-hashed, so a changed file always has a new name -
#     safe to cache forever, which removes needless revalidation round-trips.

/*
  Cache-Control: no-cache, must-revalidate

/assets/*
  ! Cache-Control
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
